{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Arrange macadamia nuts on baking tray and toast for 10 minutes (180°C). Set aside to cool.","Place cooled, toasted macadamia nuts in mixing bowl then grind <nobr>7 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add basil, lime juice, garlic, apple cider vinegar and salt then <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>.","Add oil then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a sterilised jar, seal and label then store in fridge until ready to serve (see tip)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["90 g macadamia nuts, raw, whole","50 g fresh basil","1 lime, juice only (approx. 20 g)","1 garlic clove","½ tsp apple cider vinegar","½ tsp fine sea salt","50 g extra virgin olive oil"]}],"id":"r116886","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-VDQ5rv66F6o\/XZafFHOeCsI\/AAAAAAAAgrA\/spA6ZAaKFNc0ah2U6tiT6x597GrIZuhtwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_hKJKqSFyC1zqu_Jd.png","title":"Macadamia and Lime Basil Pesto","publishedAt":"2016-04-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.1 g","fat":"118.5 g","uom":"per 1 total recipe","carbohydrates":"7.1 g","calories":"4732 kJ \/ 1131 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray, sterilised jam jar, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["<p>Recipe developed by Jenny Tschiesche BSc(Hons) Dip(ION) FdSc BANT. For more information see www.jennytschiesche.com.<\/p>","The pesto is ready for use on courgette spaghetti or to drizzle over cooked vegetables. To prepare the courgette spaghetti, use a spiralizer or julienne peeler on two medium\/large courgettes. Heat 1 tsp ghee or coconut oil and lightly sauté the courgette for 2 minutes. Add the pesto and stir until the courgette is covered. Serve and eat immediately.","Pesto will keep for 3 days in the fridge."],"basicInfo":["easy","5m","25m","1 total recipe"]}